cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about understanding the representations of deep convolutional networks trained on language tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a concept alignment method and conducts analyses with different architectures, which suggests that it could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
